HEADWORD: Retrocession
<hw>Re`tro*ces"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧trocession</ets>. See <er>Retrocede</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of retroceding.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The state of being retroceded, or granted
back.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Metastasis of an eruption or a
tumor from the surface to the interior of the body.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Retrochoir</ent>⟦br⟧
